old and black <br>{{colorstrip|w=3|h=4|gold|black}}\n||-||[[Gogonasus|Gogo fish]]<br>[[File:Gogonasus BW.jpg|92px|Gogo fish]]<ref name=WA>{{cite web| url= https://www.dpc.wa.gov.au/GuidelinesAndPolicies/SymbolsOfWA/Pages/Default.aspx | title= Symbols of Western Australia| author= Department of the Premier and Cabinet (Western Australia)|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n| -\n|-\n|}\n\n==tewitowys==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:auto;text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:64px;\"|''The Territory;''\n''The Top End'' Territory&nbsp;&nbsp;\n! style=\"width:*;\"|Coat of arms&nbsp;&nbsp;\n! style=\"width:*;\"|Floral&nbsp;&nbsp;\n! style=\"width:*;\"|Bird&nbsp;&nbsp;\n! style=\"width:*;\"|Animal&nbsp;&nbsp;\n! style=\"width:*;\"|Motto&nbsp;&nbsp;\n! style=\"width:*;\"|Colours&nbsp;&nbsp;\n! style=\"width:*;\"|Other&nbsp;&nbsp;\n|-\n||'''[[Australian Capital teritoy]]'''<br>[[File:Flag of the Australian Capital Territory.svg|92px|Australian Capital Territory]]||[[Coat of arms of Canberra]]<ref group=Note>The ACT has no arms, but as the governments of the territory and city are unified, and the city's arms are used as though they were the territory's.</ref><br>[[File:Coat of Arms of the Australian Capital Territory.svg|92px|Coat of arms of Canberra]]||[[Wahlenbergia gloriosa|Royal bluebell]]<br>[[File:Wahlenbergia gloriosa closeup.jpg|92px|Royal bluebell]]||[[Gang-gang cockatoo]]<br>[[File:Gang-gang female MJC01.jpg|92px|Gang-gang cockatoo]]||[[Brush-tailed rock-wallaby]]<br>[[File:Brush-tailed-rock-wallaby-4.jpg|92px|Brush-tailed-rock-wallaby-4]]\n|'''For the Queen, the Law and the People'''||Blue and gold <br>\n{{colorstrip|w=3|h=4|navy|gold}}\n|<ref name=ACT>{{cite web| url=http://www.cmd.act.gov.au/communication/flags | title= Emblems of Australian Capital Territory| author= ACT Govt. Chief Minister Department website|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n||'''[[Northern Territory]]'''<br>[[File:Flag of the Northern Territory.svg|92px|Northern Territor